parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description: Internal identifier of a RingCentral account or tilde (~) to indicate the account logged-in within the current session

parameters.name: extensionId
parameters.description: Internal identifier of an extension or tilde (~) to indicate the extension assigned to the account logged-in within the current session

parameters.name: extensionNumber
parameters.description: Extension number of a user. If specified, returns call log for a particular extension only

parameters.name: showBlocked
parameters.description: If 'True' then calls from/to blocked numbers are returned

parameters.name: phoneNumber
parameters.description: Phone number of a caller/callee. If specified, returns all calls (both incoming and outcoming) with the phone number specified

parameters.name: direction
parameters.description: The direction for the resulting records. If not specified, both inbound and outbound records are returned. Multiple values are accepted

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: Call type of a record. It is allowed to specify more than one type. If not specified, all call types are returned. Multiple values are accepted

parameters.name: transport
parameters.description: Call transport type. 'PSTN' specifies that a call leg is initiated from the PSTN network provider; 'VoIP' - from an RC phone. By default this filter is disabled

parameters.name: view
parameters.description: The default value is 'Simple' for both account and extension call log

parameters.name: withRecording
parameters.description: True should be specified to return recorded calls only

parameters.name: dateTo
parameters.description: The end datetime for resulting records in ISO 8601 format including timezone, for example 2016-03-10T18:07:52.534Z. The default value is current time

parameters.name: dateFrom
parameters.description: The start datetime for resulting records in ISO 8601 format including timezone, for example 2016-03-10T18:07:52.534Z. The default value is dateTo minus 24 hours

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Indicates the page number to retrieve. Only positive number values are allowed

parameters.name: perPage
parameters.description: Indicates the page size (number of items)
